Our Journey
 
 










More Than 50 Years of Automotive Excellence and Innovation
Cooper Standard has a long tradition of providing customers with the highest quality and most innovative solutions in sealing systems, fuel and brake delivery systems, fluid transfer systems and anti-vibration systems. We continue to drive value through successful relationships with our customers, our world-class operations across our expanding global footprint and our commitment to innovation within our entire business.
 



Important Dates
2016
Acquired AMI Industries’ Fuel and Brake Business
2015
Acquired Huayu-Cooper Standard, China; Acquired MAPS India JV; Formed Polyrub JV, India, Sold Hard Coat Trim Product Line
2014
Sold T&E Product Line Formed INOAC JV Acquired Remaining Interest in CS France JV
2013
Acquired Jyco Sealing Technologies Business
2012
Acquired Sigit S.p.A., Acquired EDC Technology
2011
Established Cooper Standard France; Formed Sujan JV; Expanded Nishikawa Partnership; Acquired USi Inc.
2010
Emerged from Reorganization
2007
Acquired ACH – Fuel Rail
2007
Acquired Metzeler Automotive Profiles
2006
Acquired ITT Fluid Handling
2005
Acquired Gates Corp. Automotive Hose
2004
Cooper Standard Holdings Purchases Business from Cooper Tire
2000
Acquired Siebe Automotive
1999
Acquired Standard Products Company
1960
Cooper Tire Established Automotive Division

 
 
 



